-- Real Offers Kaka to Chelsea for $34 Million, Star Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2011-12-27T10:52:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/real-offers-kaka-to-chelsea-for-34-million-star-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Kaka Fee  Real  Madrid  is willing to trade Kaka to Chelsea for 22
million pounds ($34.4 million), the  Daily Star  reported.  Paris Saint-Germain and Kaka’s former team AC Milan are
also interested in hiring him, the Star said  Juventus striker Milos Krasic is Chelsea’s top transfer
target, according to  Metro . The Serbian joined Juventus from
CSKA Moscow for 12.5 million pounds in 2010.  Mancini Deal  Manchester City is offering Roberto Mancini new terms worth
5 million pounds a year, which would make him the best-paid
Premier League coach, the  Daily Mail  reported.  The Italian is likely to agree to a contract extension
through 2015 early next year, the Mail said.  Sneijder Trade  Inter Milan could trade  Wesley Sneijder  to  Manchester
United  to raise funds, the  Daily Mail  reported.  The Dutch midfielder came close to joining United in the
last offseason, according to the Mail.  ‘Big Signing’  Tottenham coach Harry Redknapp is seeking “one big
signing” after failing to land strikers Sergio Aguero and
Giuseppe Rossi last season,  the Sun  reported.  Redknapp plans to release  Steven Pienaar  and Nico Kranjcar
on loans or permanent transfers, according to the  Daily Mirror .  To contact the reporters on this story:
